I am needing to search through arrays of objects and assign the match to a variable. It seems that variable in for/if loops are scope specific so I have to use an object as a variable and use the `.update` command in the for/if loop to update it.  Anyone know a better way? Here’s what I have but its clumsy. Id like some array search/find function for this but doesn’t seem there is one.
```{# Extract total fees  from items #}
{% set total = { fee: 0 } %}  

{% for item in items %} 
    {% if some_variable == item.id %}      
      {%  do total.update({ fee: total.fee + item.rate })  %}      
    {% endif %}
{% endfor %}```
